OL,6,FPat Coomber-Wood from North
OL,7,FOxfordshire Citizens Advice says there
OL,8,Fare ways to improve your security.
OL,10,F"You can set up 2 factor
OL,11,Fauthentication where every time you
OL,12,Flog into your account it also requires
OL,13,Fyou to go onto your mobile phone and
OL,14,Fit will send you a number you need to
OL,15,Fclick on."
OL,17,F"So that way if there's somebody who's
OL,18,Fhacked into your account, if they
OL,19,Fdon't have your mobile they won't be
OL,20,Fable to get in even if they've got
OL,21,Fyour username and password."
